  "body": "My [chainhammer](https://gitlab.com/electronDLT/chainhammer) would like to automatically detect to which type of client (geth, quorum, parity, ...) it is connected, and which type of consensus (PoW, Aura, Clique, IBFT, raft, etc.) is running.\r\n\r\nRight now, my heuristics is a rather [ugly sequence of different calls](https://gitlab.com/electronDLT/chainhammer/blob/5d3494ec0810e283cddc5881600099a15b0f1609/clienttype.py#L71-125).\r\n\r\nTwo questions:\r\n\r\n1. how to best distinguish \"geth PoW\" from \"geth PoA\" and then specifically \"geth Clique\" ?\r\n1. what about adding one more call to the web3 specification which answers *all that in one go*? \r\n\r\n(Where would be the right place to post such an issue? Sorry, I do know that this is geth, and my question is more general. forgive me please - and where do you send me instead of here? Thanks).\r\n\r\n\r\n ",
