    "body": "If you request `admin.nodeInfo` from Geth, you'll get some protocol details too, and `eth` and `les` contains the chain configs:\r\n\r\nE.g.\r\n\r\n```\r\nadmin.nodeInfo.protocols.eth.config\r\n{\r\n  byzantiumBlock: 1035301,\r\n  chainId: 4,\r\n  clique: {\r\n    epoch: 30000,\r\n    period: 15\r\n  },\r\n  daoForkSupport: true,\r\n  eip150Block: 2,\r\n  eip150Hash: \"0x9b095b36c15eaf13044373aef8ee0bd3a382a5abb92e402afa44b8249c3a90e9\",\r\n  eip155Block: 3,\r\n  eip158Block: 3,\r\n  homesteadBlock: 1\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis will either contain a `clique` field or an `ethash` field.",
